"   </a>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 470px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Rheumatic subcutaneous nodules",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 390px; height: 518px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Rheumatic subcutaneous nodules are usually located near tendons or over a bony surface or prominence. The overlying skin is not inflamed and typically can be moved over the nodules. The diameter varies from a few millimeters to one to two centimeters.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"     Courtesy of Robert Sidbury, MD.",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
